<i>Though nothing can bring back</i>
<i>the happy moments we spent together,</i>

47
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:51,131
<i>I pray that God grant me</i>
<i>the joy of seeing you again.</i>

48
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:53,963
<i>That's been my constant prayer</i>

49
00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:56,971
<i>ever since we parted</i>
<i>during the war,</i>

50
00:07:57,844 --> 00:08:01,280
<i>and it's my prayer still</i>
<i>here in this remote spot</i>

51
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:05,611
<i>where Fernando and the girls</i>
<i>and I try to survive.</i>

52
00:08:08,054 --> 00:08:12,423
<i>Little but the walls are left</i>
<i>of the house you once knew.</i>

53
00:08:13,426 --> 00:08:17,829
<i>I often wonder what became</i>
<i>of everything we had there.</i>

54
00:08:18,431 --> 00:08:20,490
<i>I don't say that out of nostalgia.</i>

55
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,829
<i>It's hard to feel nostalgic</i>

56
00:08:24,036 --> 00:08:27,472
<i>after what we've been through</i>
<i>these past few years.</i>

57
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:31,568
