<i>with its movement like</i>
<i>the main gear wheel of a clock... - </i>

169
00:26:53,645 --> 00:26:57,581
<i>Someone who saw the constant</i>
<i>agitation of the honeycomb,</i>

170
00:26:58,216 --> 00:27:01,743
<i>the mysterious,</i>
<i>maddened commotion</i>

171
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:04,854
<i>of the nurse bees</i>
<i>over the nests,</i>

172
00:27:05,256 --> 00:27:09,317
<i>the teeming bridges</i>
<i>and stairways of wax,</i>

173
00:27:09,527 --> 00:27:11,927
<i>the invading spirals of the queen,</i>

174
00:27:12,897 --> 00:27:16,389
<i>the endlessly varied</i>
<i>and repetitive labors of the swarm,</i>

175
00:27:16,668 --> 00:27:19,296
<i>the relentless yet ineffectual toil,</i>

176
00:27:19,704 --> 00:27:22,696
<i>the fevered comings and goings,</i>

177
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:25,142
<i>the call to sleep always ignored,</i>

178
00:27:25,343 --> 00:27:28,073
<i>undermining the next day's work,</i>

179
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,641
<i>the final repose of death</i>

180
00:27:31,349 --> 00:27:35,012
<i>far from a place that tolerates</i>
<i>neither sickness nor tombs... - </i>

