<i>where you were.</i>

239
00:40:39,637 --> 00:40:43,095
<i>I said you were still at school.</i>

240
00:40:47,211 --> 00:40:49,076
<i>Did you go to the well?</i>

241
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:51,646
<i>Yes.</i>

242
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:54,111
<i>Did you see him?</i>

243
00:40:58,789 --> 00:41:00,484
<i>Because he doesn't know you.</i>

244
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:04,452
<i>Papa's coming!</i>

245
00:41:05,196 --> 00:41:06,686
<i>Papa's coming!</i>

246
00:41:21,345 --> 00:41:23,245
Papa, here's one.

247
00:41:50,207 --> 00:41:53,199
- Papa, here's another one.
- I'm coming.

248
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:56,972
It's bad.

249
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,342
How much you wanna bet?

250
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:01,108
Don't touch it.

251
00:42:05,389 --> 00:42:08,017
- It's good, isn't it?
- Let's see.

252
00:42:13,731 --> 00:42:15,528
Yes, sir,
that's a good mushroom.

253
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:17,132
See?

254
00:42:17,768 --> 00:42:20,464
Who knows what it's called?

255
00:42:21,305 --> 00:42:23,637
- A brittlegill.
- A flyswatter.

256
00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:26,674
No, flyswatters are poisonous.

257
00:42:29,513 --> 00:42:30,741
Look closely.

258
00:42:32,683 --> 00:42:34,116
Trum...
- Trumpet!

259
00:42:34,318 --> 00:42:35,216
Very good.

260
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:39,448
You can tell
by the brown color

261
00:42:40,090 --> 00:42:42,183
and these wavy edges.

262
00:42:45,829 --> 00:42:48,957
Papa, have you ever picked
a poisonous mushroom?

263
00:42:49,166 --> 00:42:51,293
- No. You know why?
- Why?

264
00:42:51,502 --> 00:42:54,164
Because I always do
like my grandfather told me.

265
00:42:57,641 --> 00:43:01,133
If you're not sure
a mushroom's good, don't pick it.

266
00:43:01,745 --> 00:43:05,647
Because if it's bad
and you eat it,

267
00:43:05,849 --> 00:43:10,081
it's your last mushroom,
and your last everything else too.

268
00:43:10,387 --> 00:43:12,617
You two understand?
- I do.

269
00:43:14,158 --> 00:43:16,752
Grandfather wasn't crazy
about eating them.

270
00:43:17,194 --> 00:43:19,492
What he liked
was looking for them,

271
00:43:19,697 --> 00:43:22,359
even if it meant a full day's hike.

272
00:43:22,566 --> 00:43:24,534
He never got tired.

273
00:43:25,836 --> 00:43:27,133
See that mountain?

274
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:31,139
What he called
"the mushroom garden" is up there.

275
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:34,005
You know why?
- Why?

276
00:43:34,211 --> 00:43:37,180
Because the best mushroom
grows there... - the chanterelle.

277
00:43:37,581 --> 00:43:40,607
- Why don't we go?
- It's too far.

278
00:43:40,918 --> 00:43:43,853
We'd never make it
with you two weaklings.

279
00:43:44,054 --> 00:43:45,851
We'll go some other day.

280
00:43:46,056 --> 00:43:48,422
But first you have to promise

281
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:51,124
never to tell your mother.

282
00:44:11,181 --> 00:44:12,842
Look what we have here.

283
00:44:14,718 --> 00:44:16,777
A real devil.

284
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,746
It smells so good.

285
00:44:18,956 --> 00:44:21,424
Sure, the young ones fool you,

286
00:44:21,625 --> 00:44:24,150
but the older ones
are a different story.

287
00:44:24,928 --> 00:44:26,759
Look very closely.

288
00:44:27,898 --> 00:44:30,389
Look at the color of the cap

289
00:44:31,602 --> 00:44:34,162
and the black gills.

290
00:44:35,139 --> 00:44:38,370
Never forget, girls:
This is the worst of all.

291
00:44:38,575 --> 00:44:40,566
The most poisonous.

292
00:44:41,111 --> 00:44:45,411
Whoever eats this hasn't got
a chance in the world.

293
00:45:15,713 --> 00:45:17,180
Fernando.

294
00:45:21,418 --> 00:45:22,885
See you later.

295
00:45:31,462 --> 00:45:34,090
- Good morning, Don Fernando.
- Good morning.

296
00:45:34,298 --> 00:45:36,027
We're getting a late start.

297
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:28,778
<i>- You hit me!</i>
<i>- I did not!</i>

298
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:36,982
That's enough!
Stop being so boisterous.

299
00:46:38,462 --> 00:46:40,760
- Dummy!
- Pig!

300
00:46:42,499 --> 00:46:44,433
Good Lord!

301
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:46,125
What's all this ruckus?

302
00:46:46,336 --> 00:46:48,167
- She started it.
- That's enough!

303
00:46:48,372 --> 00:46:49,999
She's lying.

304
00:46:50,207 --> 00:46:53,335
Come on.
It's time to wash up for school.

305
00:46:54,077 --> 00:46:56,477
First you get the brush wet.

306
00:46:57,514 --> 00:46:58,913
Okay.

307
00:46:59,349 --> 00:47:01,510
Then you rub it
all over your face.

308
00:47:08,258 --> 00:47:10,556
Then you get it soapy.

309
00:47:14,097 --> 00:47:16,292
Now you rub it on your face.

310
00:47:25,509 --> 00:47:26,942
Okay.

311
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:29,942
Now I shave off the little hairs?

312
00:47:30,147 --> 00:47:33,844
Yes, and then you put on
some cologne.

313
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:46,152
Mama, do you know
what a spirit is?

314
00:47:50,033 --> 00:47:52,263
You don't know and I do.

315
00:47:53,036 --> 00:47:55,129
A spirit is a spirit.

316
00:47:55,372 --> 00:47:57,670
Are they good or bad?

317
00:47:57,875 --> 00:48:00,105
With good little girls,
they're very good,

318
00:48:00,310 --> 00:48:03,211
but with bad girls,
they're very bad.

319
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:07,847
But you're always a good girl,
aren't you?

320
00:48:08,285 --> 00:48:10,185
Give me a kiss.

321
00:48:34,244 --> 00:48:35,939
It's coming!

322
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:58,453
"Now neither malice nor hatred,

323
00:49:58,662 --> 00:50:00,459
nor even the fear of change.

324
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:02,222
I only feel thirst,

325
00:50:02,432 --> 00:50:05,026
a thirst for I know not what.

326
00:50:05,902 --> 00:50:08,370
Rivers of life,
where have you gone?

327
00:50:08,572 --> 00:50:10,699
Air, I need air.

328
00:50:10,907 --> 00:50:15,435
What do you see in the darkness
that makes you silently tremble?

329
00:50:15,746 --> 00:50:18,044
I see not
but only stare like a blind man

330
00:50:18,415 --> 00:50:20,212
facing straight into the sun.

331
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:24,816
I shall fall
where the fallen never rise."

332
00:52:09,559 --> 00:52:11,959
"To... my...

333
00:52:12,162 --> 00:52:13,823
dear...

334
00:52:14,431 --> 00:52:17,696
misanthrope."

335
00:54:29,399 --> 00:54:31,367
Come here.

336
00:55:44,908 --> 00:55:46,933
What's wrong with you?

337
00:59:04,307 --> 00:59:07,470
Come on, get up.
Stop playing around.

338
01:00:18,247 --> 01:00:20,613
He's not here anymore.
He's gone.

339
01:01:02,625 --> 01:01:06,391
Isabel, tell me what happened.

340
01:01:54,677 --> 01:01:56,406
Milagros!

341
01:04:37,440 --> 01:04:40,466
- Careful, you'll get burnt.
- Isabel!

342
01:04:40,676 --> 01:04:42,371
Careful, Raquel.

343
01:05:58,254 --> 01:06:00,188
What are you doing here, child?

344
01:06:00,556 --> 01:06:03,389
Come on, let's go.

345
01:06:04,460 --> 01:06:07,691
Let's go home.
Your father's back.

346
01:06:10,333 --> 01:06:11,823
Let's go.

347
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:14,659
Come on, let's go.

348
01:09:52,821 --> 01:09:54,846
Where were you?

349
01:10:05,568 --> 01:10:07,365
Where were you?

350
01:11:20,276 --> 01:11:21,709
Here.

351
01:14:29,498 --> 01:14:31,159
Hello.

352
01:14:32,801 --> 01:14:34,325
<i>Come in.</i>

353
01:14:40,108 --> 01:14:42,372
<i>- May I, sir?</i>
- Come in.

354
01:14:44,146 --> 01:14:46,637
- He's here.
- I'll be right there.

355
01:21:07,863 --> 01:21:09,421
Ana, come here!

356
01:27:57,372 --> 01:27:59,499
Get back!

357
01:28:10,118 --> 01:28:12,518
Ana, what happened to you?

358
01:28:38,479 --> 01:28:42,074
- Miguel, how is she?
- Fine. Still a little weak.

359
01:28:42,617 --> 01:28:45,745
She hardly sleeps.
She won't eat or speak.

360
01:28:46,020 --> 01:28:47,783
Light bothers her.

361
01:28:48,756 --> 01:28:51,919
She looks our way
but doesn't recognize us.

362
01:28:52,760 --> 01:28:55,388
It's as if we didn't exist.

363
01:29:05,106 --> 01:29:08,872
Ana is still a very small child.

364
01:29:09,377 --> 01:29:12,972
She's under the effect
of a powerful experience.

365
01:29:13,648 --> 01:29:15,445
But she'll get over it.

366
01:29:18,353 --> 01:29:19,650
Really, Miguel?

367
01:29:21,122 --> 01:29:25,058
Bit by bit
she'll begin to forget.

368
01:29:28,396 --> 01:29:31,627
The important thing is
that your daughter's alive.

369
01:29:31,933 --> 01:29:33,628
She's alive.

370
01:29:44,512 --> 01:29:45,877
She's gone to sleep.

371
01:29:46,080 --> 01:29:48,071
Don Miguel, she's asleep.

372
01:29:48,282 --> 01:29:50,773
Give her this medicine.
The dose is right here.

373
01:29:50,985 --> 01:29:53,954
Yes, sir.
I'll go right to the pharmacy.

374
01:29:55,857 --> 01:29:59,054
She should eat.
Something easy to digest.

375
01:29:59,260 --> 01:30:01,387
Soup without too much fat,

376
01:30:01,896 --> 01:30:03,955
a boiled egg.

377
01:30:06,167 --> 01:30:09,159
And you need rest too, Teresa,

378
01:30:09,370 --> 01:30:11,531
as much as she does.

379
01:30:12,673 --> 01:30:17,076
If anything happens, send Milagros
for me. I'll come right away.

380
01:30:17,278 --> 01:30:18,836
Yes, Miguel.

381
01:32:21,536 --> 01:32:25,472
<i>Someone to whom I recently</i>
<i>showed my glass beehive,</i>

382
01:32:25,840 --> 01:32:30,209
<i>with its movement like</i>
<i>the main gear wheel of a clock... - </i>

383
01:32:31,279 --> 01:32:35,238
<i>Someone who saw the constant</i>
<i>agitation of the honeycomb,</i>

384
01:32:35,750 --> 01:32:39,242
<i>the mysterious,</i>
<i>maddened commotion</i>

385
01:32:39,453 --> 01:32:42,286
<i>of the nurse bees</i>
<i>over the nests,</i>

386
01:32:42,890 --> 01:32:46,326
<i>the teeming bridges</i>
<i>and stairways of wax,</i>

387
01:32:47,295 --> 01:32:49,923
<i>the invading spirals...</i>

388
01:35:35,296 --> 01:35:37,196
<i>If you're his friend,</i>

389
01:35:37,398 --> 01:35:41,198
<i>you can talk to him</i>
<i>whenever you want.</i>

390
01:35:41,469 --> 01:35:43,562
<i>Just close your eyes</i>

391
01:35:43,771 --> 01:35:46,239
<i>and call him.</i>

392
01:35:47,808 --> 01:35:49,639
"<i>It's me, Ana."</i>

393
01:35:53,481 --> 01:35:55,210
"<i>It's me, Ana."</i>


